messages.content:
Two things to compare: the source-code shape (DSL syntax) and the rendered-image aesthetic.

## Source-code shape

Structurizr DSL is one file (`workspace.dsl`) containing model + all views. Element types are fixed (`person`, `softwareSystem`, `container`, `component`, `deploymentNode`) — no custom kinds. Categorization uses **tags + styles** instead of custom element kinds. Sequence/iteration flows use a `dynamic` view with numbered ordering.

L1 in Structurizr DSL would look roughly like:

```
workspace "Knowledge Compiler" "Multi-tenant SaaS..." {
  model {
    pm = person "Product Manager" "Asks about system behavior..."
    builder = person "SaaS Builder" "Ships the platform..." {
      tags "external"
    }

    kc = softwareSystem "Knowledge Compiler" "Ingests fragments..." {
      gw = container "API Gateway / Console" "Query UI, admin console..." "Web app"
      conn = container "Source Connectors" "..." "Service"
      // ...
    }

    slack = softwareSystem "Slack" "..." { tags "external" }
    llm = softwareSystem "Cloud LLM Providers" "..." { tags "external" }

    pm -> kc "Queries, reviews changes"
    slack -> kc "Webhooks" "HTTPS"
    kc -> llm "Extraction, reasoning, generation" "HTTPS"
  }

  views {
    systemContext kc "L1Context" {
      title "L1 — Knowledge Compiler in Context"
      include *
      autoLayout
    }

    container kc "L2Containers" {
      include *
      autoLayout
    }

    component kc.extract "L3Extraction" {
      include *
      autoLayout
    }

    dynamic kc "WritePath" "Write Path — Ingest to Merged PR" {
      slack -> kc.conn "New event"
      kc.conn -> kc.ingest "Normalized fragment + metadata"
      // numbered steps...
    }

    deployment kc "Production" "MultiTenancy" {
      deploymentNode "Tenant A" {
        containerInstance kc.claims
        containerInstance kc.raw
      }
      // ...
    }

    styles {
      element "external" { background "#cccccc" }
    }
  }
}
```

Conceptually similar to LikeC4, just more compact and with tags instead of custom kinds.

## Rendered image aesthetic

| Aspect | LikeC4 | Structurizr |
|---|---|---|
| Native renderer style | Modern, polished, designer-look, dark gradients optional | Canonical "C4 model boxes" — title / [type-label] / description / technology, the same look as on c4model.com |
| Sequence/dynamic view | Renders as a flow diagram with numbered steps | Renders as a sequence diagram (with PlantUML backend) — proper actor lanes |
| Recognition | "That looks distinctive — what's that?" | "That's a C4 diagram." Instant recognition for anyone who's seen Simon Brown's C4 model docs |

For a serious technical doc, Structurizr's canonical look is more immediately legible to anyone familiar with C4 — it's literally the look from the spec. LikeC4's look is prettier but more idiosyncratic.

## Tooling story

This is where Structurizr meaningfully differs:

- **Structurizr Lite** (Docker): `docker run -p 8080:8080 -v $(pwd):/usr/local/structurizr structurizr/lite` → full web UI with all views, browser-based PNG/SVG export. No npm, no Playwright, no Node.
- **Structurizr CLI** (Java): `brew install structurizr-cli` then `structurizr-cli export -workspace workspace.dsl -format svg` (or mermaid, plantuml, dot) — produces files per view directly. Single dependency: Java runtime.
- **PlantUML backend**: PNG/SVG via `plantuml.jar` (same Java toolchain) — clean, no headless browser.

Compared to LikeC4 + Playwright (~250MB Chromium), Structurizr CLI is a single Java JAR + plantuml.jar (~30MB total) and produces native SVG.

## Gaps that don't change

Neither Structurizr DSL nor LikeC4 supports state diagrams or class diagrams. Same limitation either way — the atom-lifecycle state and Atom data-model class diagram still need mermaid (or to be converted to tables).

## Net read

If your priority is **lightweight tooling + recognizable C4 aesthetic + SVG output without Chromium**, Structurizr DSL is the more pragmatic choice. If your priority is **modern aesthetic and tighter inline-with-markdown story** (when that story matures), LikeC4 wins.

Want me to retarget the migration to Structurizr DSL?
